title: frostiron / Those Sinned Against
body:

word count: 185.6k

When Asgard invades Earth - led by a huge blond man in a red cape and wielding a massive warhammer - it takes six months for Tony Stark to come up with a plan to turn things around: let himself be taken prisoner, and bring the Asgardians down from the inside.

But it takes less than an hour for the plan to get away from him, thanks to the black-haired Asgardian prince who takes personal - very personal - charge of him.

title: winteriron / Nothin’ You Can Prove
body:
LINK

word count: 3.3k

“I’m serious, Stevie.”

“I know you are,” Steve said, but he had that stupid little grin that meant he absolutely did not know how serious Bucky was. “I’m sure you’ll be very good for each other.”

Bucky scoffed. “No shit. I’m not marrying him on a whim.“

“You’re not even dating him yet,” Steve pointed out oh-so-helpfully.

summary: Avengers star 'Thor' spotted in India, will shoot with these Bollywood actors
title: Avengers star 'Thor' spotted in India, will shoot with these Bollywood actors
body:
Avengers star and Thor famed Chris Hemsworth secretly arrived in India to shoot for an upcoming Netflix thriller ‘Dhaka’. The Hollywood actor will begin his shoot with Indian talented actors like Randeep hooda and Manoj Bajpayee. The actor is currently in Ahmadabad and will soon leave for Mumbai.



As per report, Hemsworth was secretly spotted at Ahmadabad airport, where he clicked selfies with fans.

Before he had visited India in 2015, when he traveled out to Delhi, Agra, Leh, Goa and Dharamshala.

Dhaka, created by his MCU directors Joe and Anthony Russo, is a thriller set in India and Bangladesh. The movie will be directed by debutante Sam Hargrave, who has graduated on from playing Chris Evans’ stunt double in the ongoing Marvel films.

The film is an action thriller in which Hemsworth’s character will help in saving a kidnapped Indian kid from the Bangladeshi city Dhaka. As per Deadline, the film will be shot in India and Thailand.

The Russos and Hemsworth recently finished the last round of shooting on Avengers 4.

Read the full article
